## Types of changes

- [ ] Bugfix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)
- [x] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)

## Proposed changes

Part of #5125.

Allows a node to have actions that can be triggered from the context menu.

### Concept

If a node definition contains the `contextMenu` property, its contents will be shown in the `Show node actions` section of the context menu.

```js
RED.nodes.registerType('example', {
    defaults: {},
    contextMenu: [
        { label: 'Click me', onselect: function () { RED.notify("Here's Johnny") } }
    ],
});
```

This property will have the same characteristics as menu items:

```ts
interface MenuItemOptions {
        direction?: string;
        disabled?: boolean;
        group?: boolean;
        href?: string;
        icon?: string;
        id?: string;
        label?: string;
        local?: boolean;
        onselect?: string | ((state?: boolean) => void);
        options?: MenuItemOptions[];
        selected?: boolean;
        setting?: string;
        shortcut?: { scope: string; key: string; user?: boolean };
        sublabel?: string;
        toggle?: boolean;
        visible?: boolean;
}

Type ContextMenu = MenuItemOptions[] | ((this: Node) => MenuItemOptions[]);
```

