### Current Behavior

Select Input (typed input) values can only be strings

### Expected Behavior

It should allow other data types such as arrays, objects, numbers

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Create a select input where the values are objects or arrays, or arrays of objects.

```js
const elm = $(".node-input-select);
elm.typedInput({
      types: [
        {
          options: [{ value: [{ a: "a"}], label: "a" }, { value: [{b: "b"}], label: "b" }],
        },
      ],
    })

```
or
```js
const elm = $(".node-input-select);
elm.typedInput({
      types: [
        {
          options: [{ value: { a: "a"}, label: "a" }, { value:  { b: "b"}, label: "b" }],
        },
      ],
    })
```
or

in this case the number becomes a string
```js
const elm = $(".node-input-select);
elm.typedInput({
      types: [
        {
          options: [{ value: 1, label: "1" }, { value: 2 , label: "2" }],
        },
      ],
    })

```

2. select a value
3. save the node
4. deploy the changes
5. reload the page
6. open the node and assert the value isnt selected

