I found a work around by using axios node and then the http request works as before:
![image](https://github.com/node-red/node-red/assets/108009649/3096c957-5da0-4e2d-bb5c-2622a5438420)




### Expected Behavior

Give the current price in the UI

See the images at https://github.com/hansvanlin/SMA-Tripower-5.0---Active-Power-Control/tree/main

### Steps To Reproduce

Just press time stamp 
Respond is current price below the node.
On previous node-red version it was working good 

