When working with the node-red-nodes-test-helper I stumbled on the change node, which does not call the second on 'input' callback.

```
        const other_node = helper.getNode('other');
        other_node.on('input', function(msg:Object){
          done() 
        })
        other_node.receive({})
```
This test fails for the change node and many others, which are listed below.
The correct behavior would help testing flows with the node-red-node-test-helper, because any incoming msg could be checked.


I found the error in <https://github.com/node-red/node-red/blob/dc7fef63952548277d7759c327ce2909fdce0a3c/packages/node_modules/%40node-red/runtime/lib/nodes/Node.js#L218> starting in line 218:

```
 } else if (node._inputCallbacks) {
                // Multiple callbacks registered. Call each one, tracking eventual completion
                var c = node._inputCallbacks.length;
                for (var i=0;i<c;i++) {
                    var cb = node._inputCallbacks[i];
                    if (cb.length === 2) {
                        c++;
                    }
                    try {
                        cb.call(
                            node,
                            arg,
                            function() { node.send.apply(node,arguments) },
                            function(err) {
                                c--;
                                if (c === 0) {
                                    node._complete(arg,err);
                                }
                            }
                        );
                    } catch(err) {
                        node.error(err,arg);
                    }
                }
```
Many nodes, including the change node, **always** call the done function:
```
 function(err) {
      c--;
      if (c === 0) {
          node._complete(arg,err);
      }
 }
```
which results in skipping the second callback, because `c` is reduced and the for loop stops.
