If an output of an http request node is split, and the message contains a reference to a msg output from a http-in node, the msg cloning causes an exception which is uncaught, and leaves the flow in a bit of a limbo state.
If the split is removed the flow works.
If the split is done after a function node, the exception is caught and reported in NR on the function node (i.e. where the clone occurs).

This issue is about the http-request node not catching the exception and getting into a bad state (stays at requesting).  There may be other nodes which are affected by exceptions in clone....
The state may get worse if it's an https endpoint or behind HAProxy (got nasty NR very busy scenarios which I could not explain, but which did not occur with direct http access to the NR endpoint).

