In `/red/api/theme.js`, you currently look for files provided in the theme settings, and serve them so that they are accessible from the editor.

With Express 3.x, using `sendfile()`, it was perceived that relative paths were relative to where the application is running.

However, in Express 4.x, you must explicitly define the root on `res.sendFile()` or provide an absolute path.

Providing a second parameter of `{ root : __dirname}` would again allow paths relative to where NR is running to be used.

**`red/api/theme.js:45-47`**

from

```
app.get(url,function(req, res) {
    res.sendFile(file);
});
```

to

```
app.get(url,function(req, res) {
        res.sendFile(file, {root: __dirname});
});
```

