Hi there,

I am using Node-RED programmatically and it looks like the `RED.start()` returned Promise is not the "expected" one. Currently, we are getting back the Promise of `redNodes.load()`, but at the end of this there are two async calls:

``` js
redNodes.loadFlows();
comms.start();
```

This leads to your `RED.start().then(function () { /* called to soon */ })` being called before your flows are loaded and actually started.

This pull-request just add those two calls to the Promise chain:

``` js
// red/server.js
return redNodes.load().then(function () {
  // ... untouched
  return redNodes.loadFlows();
}).then(function () {
  return comms.start();
}).otherwise(/* untouched */);
```

and also returns the Promise of `comms.start()`:

``` js
// red/comms.js
return Users.default().then(function(anonymousUser) { /* untouched */ });
```
